                            </div>

                            <div id="collapse3a" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="heading3a" data-parent="#accordion3">
                                <div class="card-body text-justify">
                                    The Department may request for evidence of training during facility audits/inspections at any time.
                                    While working in the facility/plant/location, the trainee should ensure that they always have in their
                                    possession their MISTDO card or Number/ID.
                                    Failure to provide this could lead to possible sanctions.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-header" id="heading3b">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    <button class="btn btn-success collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3b" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3b">
                                        Do I need to be accredited by OGISP before I can register as a Training Provider on MISTDO?
                                    </button>
                                </h5>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse3b" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading3b" data-parent="#accordion3">
                                <div class="card-body text-justify">
                                    Yes! All companies operating in the Nigerian Oil and Gas Industry require an Oil and Gas Industry Service Permit (OGISP).
                                    However, accreditation for the MISTDO program has been incorporated into the OGISP platform.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-header" id="heading3c">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    <button class="btn btn-success collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3c" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3c">
                                        Who can be a Training Provider?
                                    </button>
                                </h5>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse3c" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading3c" data-parent="#accordion3">
                                <div class="card-body text-justify">
                                    Any company that has the requisite infrastructure/competencies and meet all preset
                                    requirements by DPR to carry out the training(s) can be a Training Provider.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-header" id="heading3d">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    <button class="btn btn-success collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3d" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3d">
                                        Is there an age limit for trainee registration?
                                    </button>
                                </h5>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse3d" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading3d" data-parent="#accordion3">
                                <div class="card-body text-justify">
                                    Minimum age for hazardous work in Nigeria is eighteen (18) years (Source: Labour Act, 2004).
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-header" id="heading3d">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    <button class="btn btn-success collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3d" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3d">
                                        How can a MISTDO training center which has been accredited by DPR be verified by members of the public?
                                    </button>
                                </h5>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse3d" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="heading3d" data-parent="#accordion3">
                                <div class="card-body text-justify">
                                    All accredited MISTDO training providers are published on the MISTDO portal.
                                    In addition, any prospective trainee or customer
                                    may request to view the DPR accreditation permit to confirm its validity.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-header" id="heading3d">
                                <h5 class="mb-0">
                                    <button class="btn btn-success collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse3d" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse3d">
                                        Can a training certificate issued by a non- DPR accredited training center be recognized?
                                    </button>
